  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishment of a multi-sectoral strategy for the control of brucellosis in the main peri-urban dairy production zones of West and Central Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DFID has reduced its funding to two existing BBSRC / DFID funding programmes, ZELS http://www.bbsrc.ac.uk/research/international/zels/ and SCPRID http://www.bbsrc.ac.uk/documents/1210-scprid-pdf/.  Both programmes involve a number of different funding agencies, UK research is funded by the Research Councils and additionally DSTL (ZELS), research in developing countries was funded by DFID and in-country partners such as DBT, India (SCPRID) with additional support from BMGF.  Countries / international research organisations involved in the programmes are: 
SCPRID: CGIAR plus Australia, Bangladesh, Burkina Faso, Denmark, Ethiopia, India, Japan Kenya, Mexico, South Africa, Tanzania, Uganda, USA
ZELS: FAO (UN) plus Australia, Bangladesh, Kenya, Mayanmar, New Zealand, Niger, Pakistan, Senegal, South Africa, Switzerland, Tanzania, USA, Vietnam,
Following dicussions with BEIS it has been agreed that the projects would be supported by a combination of GCRF individual allocation (year 1) and other Government ODA funding streams.</narrative>
  </description>
